http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Music Curriculum Standards for Kindergarten.
Singing - Students will sing alone and with others, a varied repertoire of music.
Develop skill in singing simple songs.
Explore high and low pitches.
Explore upward and downward direction vocally.
Playing Instruments - Students will perform on instruments, alone and with others, a varied repertoire of music.
Develop skill in reproducing steady beat.
Explore playing long/short and fast/slow sounds.
Play high and low sounds.
Improvising - Students will improvise melodies, variations, and accompaniments.
Create instrumental sounds to accompany songs, poems, and stories.
Create vocal sounds to accompany songs, poems, and stories.
Improvise creative movement to accompany songs, poems, stories, and listening examples.
Composing - Students will compose and arrange music within specific guidelines.
Create short compositions using a variety of sounds.
Reading and Notating - Students will read and notate music.
Interpret iconic representations of steady beat.
Interpret iconic representation of melodic direction.
Listening and Analyzing - Students will listen to, analyze, and describe music.
Recognize same and different sections in familiar pieces of music.
Recognize the difference between voices and instruments.
Recognize musical characteristics in selected pieces of music.
Evaluating - Students will evaluate music and music performances.
Evaluate musical performances based on an age-appropriate criteria.
Develop and evaluate appropriate audience behaviors during a performance.
Interdisciplinary Connections - Students will understand relationships between music, the other arts, and disciplines outside the arts.
Experience relationships between music and dance, visual art, and/or theatre.
Experience relationships between music and language arts.
Historical and Cultural Connections - Students will understand music in relation to history and culture.
Experience music from various historical periods and cultures.
